<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
GeglBlend

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Abstract class that represents blend modes.

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
This is the abstract class that represents a foreground and background
image combined in a blend mode. This class has an <literal>opacity</literal>
property which is used as multiplier for the alpha channel of the foreground.
</para>

<para>
Blend modes are described by the following formula for the case of 
premultiplied images (f,fa), (b,ba), with result (c,ca).
</para>

<literallayout>
c = (1-fa)*b + (1-ba)*f + fa*ba*blend(f/fa, b/ba)
ca = fa + ba - fa*ba
</literallayout>

<para>
Different blend modes define the function blend differently. 
For example the Multiply mode defines blend(x,y) = x*y.
</para>

